<!--
Student Management System - HTML views for an MVC app
Files included below (copy each into separate files in your project):
  - views/_header.html    -> common header/nav
  - views/_footer.html    -> common footer
  - views/index.html      -> list students (GET /students)
  - views/create.html     -> create form (GET /students/create)
  - views/edit.html       -> edit form (GET /students/:id/edit)
  - views/show.html       -> student details (GET /students/:id)
  - public/css/styles.css -> shared styles
  - public/js/main.js     -> client-side JS (validation + delete confirmation)

These are plain, framework-agnostic HTML templates. In your MVC server (e.g., Express, Laravel, ASP.NET, Spring), render these views and supply `students`, `student`, and form action URLs as appropriate.
-->

